Step 1 — TRANSLATE the visual into algebra
  "symmetry" → reflection formula: reflected = 2*axis - x
  "closest"  → distance formula
  "angle"    → atan2
  "overlap"  → bounding box intersection
  "collinear"→ cross product = 0

Step 2 — AVOID floating point wherever possible
  Instead of axis = (a+b)/2.0, use axisSum = a+b
  Instead of dist = sqrt(dx²+dy²), compare dist² = dx²+dy²
  When you must use doubles, never use ==, use Math.abs(a-b) < 1e-9

Step 3 — HANDLE overflow proactively
  Coordinates up to 10^8
  dx*dx can reach 10^16 → use long, not int
  Always cast before multiplying: (long)dx * dx

Step 4 — ENCODE cleverly for O(1) lookup
  Store points as "x,y" strings in a HashSet
  Store slopes as "dy/gcd,dx/gcd" strings to avoid float comparison
  Store angles as sorted doubles in a List

Step 5 — HANDLE edge cases specific to geometry
  Points at the same location (duplicates)
  Points ON the axis/line itself
  Single point
  All points collinear